# Go backend

**Module path:** `github.com/daveontour/aimuseum` (imports must use this prefix).

## Layers (typical new API)

1. `internal/handler/<domain>_handler.go` — HTTP
2. `internal/api/router/router.go` — register route
3. `internal/service/<domain>_service.go` — business logic
4. `internal/repository/<domain>_repo.go` — SQL via pgx

## Database

- Schema source: `sqlc/schema.sql`; migrations: `internal/database/migrations/` (`NNN_description.sql`).
- After schema changes: `make generate` (sqlc) when the project uses it; keep repo code consistent with schema.

## Style

- Follow existing error handling and logging in neighboring handlers/services.
- New endpoints belong in the router with the same middleware/style as siblings.
